White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer gave a press briefing during President Trump's flight to Mar-a-Lago. He mentioned that President Trump ordered flags to be flown at half-mast in honor of Senator John Glenn, and also discussed the President's participation in the Wounded Warrior Project Soldier Ride. Spicer provided details on the President's schedule during his visit to Mar-a-Lago, including a dinner with Chinese President Xi Jinping and meetings focused on trade and national security. He also mentioned that Vice President Mike Pence will be traveling to Asia, and that the President will be hosting the Secretary General of NATO next week. Spicer addressed questions regarding the recent gas attack in Syria, border security, the recusal of Chairman Nunes from the House Intel investigation on Russia, and the removal of Steve Bannon from the National Security Council. He also mentioned that the President's nominee for Supreme Court Justice, Judge Neil Gorsuch, will likely be sworn in on Monday or Tuesday. Spicer concluded the briefing by discussing ongoing discussions on the healthcare bill and expressing confidence in Speaker Ryan's ability to get it done.